    <h1>Guide to perform a voluntary exit for your validator using EthDO</h1>
    <p>At some point, you maight want to exit your validator and obtain your initial deposit plus remaining rewards back to your wallet (assuming you have a withdrawal address associated with your validator). This guide show how to perform the exit using <a href="https://github.com/wealdtech/ethdo" target="_blank">Ethdo</a> tool.</p>
    <p>Ethdo tool is usually used on both side - on the side of staking node to generate offline-preparation.json file and on the client side to generate exit keys with a use of the offline-preparation.json file. However, as offline-preparation.json file can be downloaded from internet, it's possible to perform the exit externally - without a need to have access to any staking node. This guide sumamrizes both options.</p>
    <p>Exiting with using ethdo consists of 2 steps:</p>
