            <h2>Sources preparation</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc my-4">
                <li><h3>Download Ethdo</h3>
                    <p>ethdo is a command-line tool for managing common tasks in Ethereum. In this guide it will be used to (pre)sign voluntary exit for your validators.</p>
                    <p>Download the etho archive and the associated checksum file for OS you are going to generate exit keys on. <strong>Note: I recommend to use Linux option, as it allows simplest way to "run" in a secure offline mode (see <a href="#generation">step generation</a>).</strong></p>
                    <amp-selector class="tabs-with-flex" role="tablist" keyboard-select-mode="focus">
<div id="tab1" role="tab" aria-controls="tabpanel1" option selected>Desktop UI</div>
    <div id="tabpanel1" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab1">
        <p>Go to <a href="https://github.com/wealdtech/ethdo/releases" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">ethdo github</a> and download latest version for Operating system you are going to generate exit keys on.</p>
    </div>
<div id="tab2" role="tab" aria-controls="tabpanel2" option selected>Linux</div>
    <div id="tabpanel2" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab2">
        <p>Open terminal and process following steps to get ethdo tool.</p>
        <h4>Download the etho archive and the associated checksum file</h4>
<pre><code>wget https://github.com/wealdtech/ethdo/releases/download/v1.36.1/ethdo-1.36.1-linux-amd64.tar.gz
wget https://github.com/wealdtech/ethdo/releases/download/v1.36.1/ethdo-1.36.1-linux-amd64.tar.gz.sha256</code></pre>
        <h4>Make sure ethdo checksum matches</h4>
<pre><code>sha256sum ethdo-1.36.1-linux-amd64.tar.gz
cat ethdo-1.36.1-linux-amd64.tar.gz.sha256</code></pre>
        <p>Both of these output values should have matching checksum. If they do not match, there might be a security issue and you should seek further support.</p>
        <h4>Extract the ethdo archive</h4>
        <pre><code>tar xvf ethdo-1.36.1-linux-amd64.tar.gz</code></pre>
    </div>
